/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		OwlEvolution.pr_PaymentsLoadToOpenAccess					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	16/11/2018
											
Description:
===========

The proc loads the Owl Hierarchy Payments into the OpenAccess Owl Payment Hierarchy Download
table i.e.
from:	OwlEvolution.sa_SwiftLogging_PaymentToHierarchy
To:		dbo.owoa_OwlHierarchyPayments

This process uses a MERGE statement. However, there is no DELETE component in case the staging table
breaks and we end up with an empty staging table. In this scenario we wouldn't want this process to
remove all the payments from the download table.

This proc is called as follows:
	
	exec [OwlEvolution].[pr_PaymentsLoadToOpenAccess] 'Owl', 'OpenAccess'
	
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
28/11/2018	A Groves	Removed processing to identify the latest date from which changes should
						be drawn as this was stopping the standing order details from being updated.
13/12/2018	A Groves	Warranty fix: Exclude payments where the Enterprise UID is null. This can
						occur where the RoleAdviserUID is the Owl Orphan Override pot code 1011623.
10/10/2019	S Campbell	Fix the join to mstt_policies as caseid isn't alway present (use payment id back to transaction) CR#26472
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [OwlEvolution].[pr_PaymentsLoadToOpenAccess_Backup20200327AG]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)

AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
